 class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 30, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xrt1665702692493.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xrt1665702692493.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xrt1665702692493.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xrt1665702692493\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__uinstdel_404861\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Delete a component instance.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__topic_d121388e1_d121389e1_d121390e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xrt1665702692493_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__codeblock_mj5_fdb_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">long uinstdel (UHACT hInst, long* pProcError);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__topic_d86147e1_d86148e1_d86149e1_d86150e1_d86151e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d859649e61\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__parml_avt_gdb_1wb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hInst</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">The instance handle as returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstnew</code>. </dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pProcError</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">(Output) The ProcScript error status, that is, the same value that would be\n                  returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">deleteinstance</code> in <code class=\"ph codeph\">$procerror</code>. If you\n                  are not interested in this output, supply a zero value instead of a pointer.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__topic_d86152e1_d86153e1_d86154e1_d86155e1_d86156e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d859649e99\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__d5955e20\">For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return\n        Codes\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__topic_d86157e1_d86158e1_d86159e1_d86160e1_d86161e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d859649e108\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__topic_d86162e1_d86163e1_d86164e1_d86165e1_d86166e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d859649e120\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__p_d121418e1_d121419e1_d121420e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstdel</code> must be used to delete an\n            instance that was created by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstnew</code>. It is not recommended to delete\n            an instance whose handle was returned by <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinstopn</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__p_d121421e1_d121422e1_d121423e1\">Deleting the instance does not delete the instance\n            handle. After deleting an instance, its handle still needs to be freed by calling\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufreeh</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__section_rnv_l2b_1wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d859649e143\">Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and\n            uopract</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC\n            operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake\n            of brevity.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104xrt1665702692493_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"xrt1665702692493__codeblock_sqv_42b_1wb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n\nvoid main (void)\n{\nUHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */\nUHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */\nUHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */\nlong opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */\n\n/* Create the environment */\nuecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &amp;hEnv);\n/* Instantiate service MYSVC */\nuinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, 0);\n\nuinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &amp;hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */\nuopract (hOp, &amp;opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */\nuinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */\n\nufreeh (&amp;hOp); /* Free the operation */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free the instance */\nuedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */\nreturn 0; // on success\t\t\t\t\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jhh1665702691902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Call-In API Return Codes</a><p>Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qrb1665702691766.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ufreeh</a><p>Free (delete) a handle.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iou1665702692361.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinstnew</a><p>Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533874\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533874\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uinstdel Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 30, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Delete a component instance. Explain this code long uinstdel (UHACT hInst, long* pProcError); Copy Parameters hInst The instance handle as returned by uinstnew . pProcError (Output) The ProcScript error status, that is, the same value that would be returned by deleteinstance in $procerror . If you are not interested in this output, supply a zero value instead of a pointer. Return Values For more information, see the \"Call-In API Return Codes\" topic. Use Library: ucall Description uinstdel must be used to delete an instance that was created by uinstnew . It is not recommended to delete an instance whose handle was returned by uinstopn . Deleting the instance does not delete the instance handle. After deleting an instance, its handle still needs to be freed by calling ufreeh . Example: uecreate, uedelete, ufreeh, uinstdel, uinstnew, uinstopr, and uopract The following simple call-in program shows how to activate the EXEC operation of the service MYSVC. As usual, error checking has been omitted for the sake of brevity. Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> void main (void) { UHACT hEnv; /* Uniface environment */ UHACT hIn; /* Instance handle */ UHACT hOp; /* Operation handle */ long opStat; /* Activate status return parameter */ /* Create the environment */ uecreate(1, 0, 0, \"my.asn\", 0, 0, &hEnv); /* Instantiate service MYSVC */ uinstnew(hEnv, \"MYSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, 0); uinstopr(hIn, \"EXEC\", 0, &hOp); /* Instantiate the EXEC operation */ uopract (hOp, &opStat, 0); /* Activate the operation */ uinstdel(hIn, 0); /* Destroy the instance */ ufreeh (&hOp); /* Free the operation */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free the instance */ uedelete(hEnv, -1); /* Shut down the environment */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free the environment handle */ return 0; // on success } Copy Related Links Call-In API Return Codes Codes that can possibly be returned by functions from the 3GL call-in API are consistent with the values returned by the ProcScript function $procerror, unless noted otherwise. ufreeh Free (delete) a handle. uinstnew Create a new instance of a Uniface 4GL component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}